Hi=20

Sorry ... nothing deep or fundamental here.

Here is a simple question which someone may know the answer to.=20

Lets say we have a fibration p:E -> B with left adjoints Sigma_f for =
every reindexing functor f^*.  Lets say further that E has products and =
p preserves them.

Are there simple conditions under which we have

Sigma_{f \times g} (P \times Q)=20

iso

(Sigma_f P) \times (Sigma_g Q)

All the best
